cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.OS, cs.AR 

This paper deals with memory reclamation in concurrent data structures, which is a topic that falls under the categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Operating Systems (cs.OS), and Architecture (cs.AR). However, given the focus on wait-free memory reclamation, which is a key challenge in concurrent programming, the most likely categories are cs.DC and cs.DS. The paper also discusses the implementation of the scheme on specific architectures, which further supports the inclusion of cs.AR. The other categories are less likely but still relevant to the paper's content.
